<section>
  <h2>About the Program</h2>
  <p>This website is part of the LSU College of Engineering's Fall 2025 Mock Interview Program. It provides a realistic job description for students to practice their interviewing skills in a simulated environment.</p>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>About OCC’s Future Engineers</h2>
  <p><strong>OCC’s Future Engineers</strong> is a fictional company created by LSU’s Olinde Career Center. The company specializes in innovative engineering solutions across various disciplines, offering students a platform to engage in practical, real-world scenarios.</p>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>Engineer Intern – Sample Job Description</h2>
  <div class="job-description">
    <p><strong>Position:</strong> Engineer Intern</p>
    <p><strong>Location:</strong> Baton Rouge, LA</p>
    <p><strong>Description:</strong> As an Engineer Intern, you will collaborate with project engineers on evaluating existing conditions, designing structural repairs, managing construction processes, and interacting with clients and contractors.</p>

    <p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li>Design construction projects and analyze engineering problems.</li>
      <li>Calculate specifications and create technical drawings.</li>
      <li>Use CAD software for design and drafting tasks.</li>
      <li>Ensure compliance with building regulations and evaluate construction quality.</li>
      <li>Provide technical support and maintain accurate records.</li>
    </ul>

    <p><strong>Qualifications:</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li>Currently pursuing a Bachelor's degree in Engineering (Mechanical, Electrical, or related field).</li>
      <li>Strong analytical and problem-solving skills.</li>
      <li>Proficiency in Microsoft Office Suite and CAD software.</li>
      <li>Excellent communication and teamwork abilities.</li>
    </ul>

    <p><strong>Note:</strong> This is a mock job posting for educational purposes only. Only students approved for the Fall 2025 Mock Interview Program may apply.</p>
  </div>
</section>

